const title = "Bunn Slushie Machine Repair | Southern California | Ultra, Coffee Brewer Maker";
const description = "Bunn slushie machine repair Southern California, Ultra-1, Ultra-2, Ultra-NX frozen beverage dispensers. Springfield IL OEM since 1957. $120. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/bunn-slushie-machine-repair/";

const faqs = [
  { q: "Who makes Bunn slushie machines, and what's the coffee-brewer connection?", a: "Bunn-O-Matic Corporation is headquartered in Springfield, Illinois, founded in 1957 by George R. Bunn Jr. The company is best known as the OEM behind most US commercial coffee brewers, BUNN-branded coffee brewers are the standard at diners, restaurants, gas stations, convenience stores, and hospitality across the country, and the brand has dominated the commercial coffee-brewing equipment category for decades. The slushie / frozen beverage line is a secondary product category within Bunn's commercial-equipment portfolio: Bunn engineered slushie machines because the same B2B operator base (coffee shops, c-stores, juice bars, hospitality) needed frozen beverage equipment alongside coffee brewers, and the existing service relationship + parts distribution made the product extension a natural fit. For LA service, Bunn slushie machines benefit from Bunn's well-established US parts distribution + technical-service infrastructure built around the larger coffee-brewer business." },
  { q: "Which Bunn slushie machine models do you see in LA?", a: "Bunn's slushie / frozen beverage lineup centers on the Ultra Series. <b>Ultra-1</b> is the single-flavor 1-bowl unit common at small coffee shops and c-stores adding slushie to a single-product footprint. <b>Ultra-2</b> is the dual-flavor 2-bowl configuration, the most common LA install at convenience stores, juice bars, and operators wanting two flavor options in one cabinet. <b>Ultra-NX</b> is Bunn's premium spec with electronic touchpad controls + improved freeze-cycle management for higher-volume operators. Common LA install density: c-store chains across LA County, juice bars in Westside + Hollywood, convenience stores in East LA + Mid-Wilshire + South LA, plus various coffee-shop operators who added slushie alongside espresso operations. Service domain on all Ultra Series: auger motor, refrigeration system, mix pump, beater scraper assembly, control board, door seal." },
  { q: "What's the most common Bunn slushie machine failure mode?", a: "Auger motor failure is the dominant Bunn slushie service call. The auger motor drives the slushie agitation system inside the freezing cylinder, continuous-duty operation during business hours produces high cumulative motor-hours, and motor bearings + gear-train components wear out at predictable cycle counts. Symptoms: slushie freezes too hard (slurry isn't moving fast enough to maintain proper consistency), motor stalls or overheats, intermittent operation, audible bearing noise. Diagnostic sequence: verify motor electrical, test motor under load, inspect gear train, check beater/scraper alignment. Auger motor replacement is the routine service work, typical $380-$680 parts + labor. Second-most-common failure: refrigeration system issues (compressor cycling, condenser fouling, refrigerant leaks) which run higher-cost service depending on specific component." },
  { q: "Bunn vs Taylor vs Electro Freeze, what's the LA slushie landscape?", a: "Three distinct brand positions in the US commercial slushie market. <b>Taylor Company</b> (now part of Carrier Commercial Refrigeration) is the dominant overall slushie + soft-serve OEM in the US, Taylor units run at the bulk of high-volume dedicated slushie operations including movie theater chains, theme parks, and large c-store programs. <b>Electro Freeze</b> (HC Duke & Son, Wisconsin) is the second-tier player with strong restaurant + foodservice presence. <b>Bunn</b> (this page) occupies the coffee-shop + c-store + juice-bar B2B segment where the operator already runs Bunn coffee brewers and adding Bunn slushie keeps the parts + service relationship unified through one OEM. For LA service, we cover Bunn through the Bunn parts-supply channel; Taylor and Electro Freeze service routes through their respective dedicated channels (Taylor's relationship with parent Carrier Commercial, Electro Freeze through HC Duke distribution)." },
  { q: "How often should commercial slushie machines need preventive service?", a: "Bunn recommends quarterly preventive maintenance on Ultra Series slushie machines, every 90 days of continuous operation. PM scope: clean condenser coils (LA dust + grease accumulation reduces refrigeration efficiency over months), inspect + replace beater/scraper assembly if wear evident, verify auger motor function under load, check mix pump operation, inspect door seals for compression set, sanitize per food-safety code, and verify temperature setpoints + freeze-cycle timing. Operators who stay on quarterly PM schedule see substantially fewer break-fix calls and longer equipment service life. Operators who skip PM and run reactive-only service typically face auger motor failure 30-40% sooner than scheduled-maintenance operators, plus refrigeration efficiency drift that can trigger compressor failure (the most expensive single repair in slushie service). Quarterly PM service typically $180-$280 per visit for single-bowl unit, $260-$380 for dual-bowl Ultra-2." },
  { q: "What does Bunn slushie machine repair cost in LA?", a: "$120 flat commercial diagnostic, waived when you authorize the repair. Typical Bunn Ultra Series service ranges: door seal replacement $180-$280; beater/scraper assembly $220-$380; touchpad/membrane (Ultra-NX) $220-$360; mix pump replacement $260-$440; quarterly PM service $180-$380 depending on bowl count; auger motor replacement $380-$680 (most common single repair); refrigeration leak repair + recharge $480-$780; control board replacement $480-$820 (Ultra-NX higher than Ultra-1/Ultra-2); compressor replacement $850-$1,400 (major repair, repair-vs-replace conversation on older units). Most Bunn slushie service calls land $280-$680 parts + labor; compressor + control board work runs the higher end. Bunn parts distribution typical 2-5 day lead through the company's North American service network." }
];

